synthesis_method: An all-solid-state battery was prepared with a positive electrode layer containing CuS and elemental sulfur through the synthesis of a solid electrolyte with LiI, Li2S, and P2S5, followed by the manufacturing of the positive electrode layer composition by mortar mixing at specific weight ratios and subsequent ball milling, leading to the fabrication of the battery by laminating Li metal foil, the electrolyte, and the positive electrode layer composition in a Teflon cylinder under pressure.
